00:09:09.542 --> 00:09:11.954
This really should be a straight line.

00:09:11.954 --> 00:09:14.207
This is essentially plotting the slope

00:09:14.207 --> 00:09:16.606
of this curve at any point.

00:09:16.606 --> 00:09:18.872
Now, what we can think about is,

00:09:18.872 --> 00:09:21.205
because this by itself, this is telling us

00:09:21.205 --> 00:09:23.332
the marginal benefit in
terms of cars washed,

00:09:23.332 --> 00:09:25.005
but this doesn't tell
us the marginal benefit

00:09:25.005 --> 00:09:26.800
in terms of dollars.

00:09:27.107 --> 00:09:31.118
To do that we need the
marginal product revenue

00:09:31.118 --> 00:09:32.284
or you could call it the value

00:09:32.284 --> 00:09:34.351
of the marginal product of labor.

00:09:34.813 --> 00:09:36.534
Let me write that over here.

00:09:36.534 --> 00:09:41.961
We could call this the MPR,
for marginal product revenue

00:09:41.961 --> 00:09:44.010
or we could view that as the value

00:09:44.010 --> 00:09:46.676
of the marginal product of labor,

00:09:46.676 --> 00:09:47.740
but essentially we're saying

00:09:47.740 --> 00:09:51.099
okay, if we're washing 5 extra
cars from that first person

00:09:51.099 --> 00:09:53.238
and I'm going to get $5 per car wash.

00:09:53.238 --> 00:09:55.876
I have a constant marginal revenue.

00:09:55.876 --> 00:09:57.217
I am a price taker.

00:09:57.217 --> 00:09:59.957
Then I'm going to make $25
on those incremental 5 cars

00:10:00.526 --> 00:10:03.546
and if I wash 4 more cars, 4 times 5,

00:10:03.546 --> 00:10:05.546
I'm going to make $20 extra dollars.

00:10:05.546 --> 00:10:09.205
If I wash 3 extra cars, I'm
going to make $15 extra dollars.

00:10:09.205 --> 00:10:11.403
Two extra cars, $10 extra dollars.

00:10:11.403 --> 00:10:12.908
I'm just multiplying by 5 every time.

00:10:12.908 --> 00:10:16.806
This is times 5, times 5, times 5, times 5

00:10:16.806 --> 00:10:19.629
and if I wash one extra
car, times $5 per car,

00:10:19.629 --> 00:10:21.211
I'm going to make $5 extra.

00:10:21.211 --> 00:10:22.793
So, essentially we could take every point

00:10:22.793 --> 00:10:25.972
on this curve and we
could multiply it by 5

00:10:25.972 --> 00:10:28.070
to get our marginal product of revenue

00:10:28.070 --> 00:10:29.953
or marginal product revenue.

00:10:29.953 --> 00:10:32.066
